      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, it can be quite frustrating when something like your AC unit suddenly stops working without any obvious reason. While it's not extremely common for capacitors to fail without warning, it's not unheard of either. Capacitors can degrade over time due to factors like age, heat, or electrical surges, which can cause them to fail unexpectedly.\n\nOther components, such as the motor, relays, or even the thermostat, can also fail and cause similar issues. It's also possible that something external, like a power surge or a fallen tree branch, could have caused damage to the unit.\n\nIf your AC unit was working fine yesterday and now it's not, it could be due to a sudden failure of one of these components. It's always a good idea to consult with a professional to diagnose the problem accurately and safely. They can help you determine the root cause of the issue and recommend the best course of action for repair or replacement.",
